body_md_en:
A spacecraft is sent to investigate a planet of mass and radius . When the spacecraft is hovering motionless in space at a distance of 5*ₚ* from the planet's center of mass, it launches a tool package with a speed of 0. The package has a mass $m_{1}$ that is much lighter than the mass of the spacecraft. The package is launched at an elevation angle relative to the radial line connecting the planet's center of mass and the spacecraft. Determine:

- (a) the angular momentum condition of the package with respect to the planet's center of mass;
- (b) the speed of the package when it just grazes the planet's surface as a function of the angle *θ*;
- (c) the magnitude of the angle *θ* so that the package can graze the planet's surface.

